"It was an unrivaled athletic triumph.
But more than that, it really was a triumph for all humanity."
Owens devoted himself to working with youth and serving as "a special ambassador for sports," said Bush.
"Despite the many honors, his greatest satisfaction came from his work with youth," said Mrs. Owens, 74.
The silver-haired Mrs. Owens, standing outside the White House afterwards, called the event "absolutely beautiful."
